data.chText: 忧郁的；凄凉的；惨淡的；阴沉的
悲惨的状况；凄凉的环境；阴沉的天气
不熟练的；差劲的；不怎么样的
data.enText: not skilful or successful; of very low quality

data.chText: 那歌手唱了几首老歌，唱得不怎么样。
data.enText: The singer gave a dismal performance of some old songs.

data.chText: 他们最近努力想提高销售量，全是白费劲。
data.enText: Their recent attempt to increase sales has been a dismal failure .

data.chText: 我想尽量忍着不笑，但根本忍不住。
data.enText: I tried not to laugh but failed dismally (= was completely unsuccessful) .

example: the dark days of the war
a week of rainy depressing weather
the first dismal dispiriting days of November

value.def: Something that is dismal is bad in a sad or depressing way.

example.tran: 以色列在奥运会上让人沮丧的记录

example.ex: My prospects of returning to a suitable job are dismal...
example.tran: 我重新找到一个合适的工作岗位的希望很渺茫。
这是个让人沮丧的失败。

value.tran: 忧郁的;凄凉的;令人沮丧的

example.ex: He failed dismally in his opening match.

value.def: Something that is dismal is sad and depressing, especially in appearance.

example.ex: The main part of the hospital is pretty dismal but the children's ward is really lively.
example.tran: 医院的主体部分死气沉沉，但是儿科病房却充满生气。

example.ex: ...a dark dismal day with rain falling steadily...
example.tran: 天空昏暗、阴雨绵绵的一天

example.ex: You can't occupy yourself with dismal thoughts all the time.
example.tran: 不要终日陷在阴郁的思绪中。

value.tran: (尤指外表)阴暗的，阴沉的，沉闷的
